# File Extract Preview Feature (April 2026)

File extract preview feature built across 13+ sessions starting 2026-04-01. Transforms file attachment capsule tags into inline preview containers within the NSTextView editor.

**Why:** Users need to see file contents inline without opening external apps. Complements existing Quick Look hover tooltip.

**How to apply:** When working on file preview code, understand the full data flow before making changes. This feature had 6+ failed fix attempts because the systems involved (NSTextAttachment sizing, NSLayoutManager glyph caching, styleTodoParagraphs, SwiftUI/NSHostingView bridge) are deeply interconnected.

## Architecture

- `NoteFileAttachment` (in TodoEditorRepresentable.swift) -- NSTextAttachment subclass with viewMode (.tag/.medium/.full), storedFilename, cachedImageAspectRatio
- `FilePreviewOverlayView` -- NSView shell wrapping NSHostingView, follows CodeBlockOverlayView/CalloutOverlayView pattern
- `FilePreviewContent` -- SwiftUI view with header bar (filename + chevron menu, "Open in App" button) and category-specific renderers
- `Renderers/` directory -- PDFPreviewRenderer, ImagePreviewRenderer, AudioPreviewRenderer, VideoPreviewRenderer, TextPreviewRenderer, ThumbnailPreviewRenderer
- `FileHoverTooltips` -- glass pill tooltips for Quick Look + Extract actions on tag-mode attachments
- `FileCategory` enum classifies UTType into pdf/image/audio/video/text/office/other

## Critical Implementation Details

- `heightForData()` computes height reservation for the NSTextAttachment. For images, uses `cachedImageAspectRatio` (computed via CGImageSource header reading) to derive `min(contentWidth / ar, 600)`.
- `updateFilePreviewOverlays()` called synchronously (not via scheduleOverlayUpdate) -- async was a root cause of layout mismatch
- `styleTodoParagraphs()` must include `NoteFileAttachment` (with viewMode != .tag) in block attachment detection -- omission was root cause of height=1-line bug
- `isUpdating` flag must wrap replaceCharacters calls in extractStoredFile/extractFileLink to prevent textDidChange reentrancy
- Hover tooltips are viewMode-aware: only show on .tag mode, not on extracted previews
- "Open in App" button uses `Color("ButtonSecondaryBgColor")` (not glass-on-glass, not ultraThinMaterial-on-glass)
- `containerWidth` must be passed to FilePreviewOverlayView init (not set after) -- see feedback_nshostingview_width_timing.md

## Serialization

`[[file|typeIdentifier|storedFilename|originalFilename|viewMode]]` -- viewMode is optional, defaults to .tag for backward compatibility.

## Status as of 2026-04-02

Feature is functional but undergoing polish. Image width-fill and aspect-ratio-locked height just implemented. Multi-page PDF rendering deferred. Context menu (View As, Rename, Copy, Delete) works. Tag reversion resets paragraph style to prevent new-line insertion.
